    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="293"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d293">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the Director of
                        War Mobilization</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BJF1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Byrnes</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d293fn1">Sent to <persName corresp="#p_ML2"
                            >Mathewson</persName> at the White House for delivery to <persName
                            corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_ML2"
                            >Mathewson</persName> was instructed to send copies of the message to
                            <persName corresp="#p_HFJ1">Horne</persName> and to <persName
                            corresp="#p_NDM1">Nelson</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-23">23 <hi rend="smallcaps"
                                >November</hi> 1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Extremely important and urgent that I know at once whether the present schedules
                    for production and completion of landing craft can be increased during January,
                    February, March, April and May. On the assumption that landing craft takes
                    precedence over all other munitions of war will you let me know how many
                    additional landing craft by types can be delivered during the months of January,
                    February, March, April and May? List each month separately. Call conference of
                    all interested departments. Very urgent.<note n="2" xml:id="d293fn2">For an
                        account of <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>’ action on this
                        matter and for a facsimile of a private letter of November 23, 1943, from
                            <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> to <persName
                            corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>, see <persName corresp="#p_BJF1"
                            >James F. Byrnes</persName>, <hi rend="italic">All In One Lifetime</hi>
                        (New York: Harper and Brothers, 1958), pp. 202–205.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
